# Cloudflare Pages rewrites for the docs site.
#
# The OpenAPI spec is committed as `rates-engine.v1.yaml` (the
# versioned filename ties output to the `v1` namespace). External
# tooling — Postman, OpenAPI Generator, IDE plugins — auto-discovers
# at the conventional `/openapi.yaml` and `/openapi.json` paths.
#
# Without these rules, the CF Pages SPA fallback served the
# `index.html` for those paths (HTTP 200 but the wrong body),
# which broke spec-loading tools that don't validate
# Content-Type. The 200-status rewrite (vs 301) keeps the URL
# stable so the discovered path is the path the tool keeps using.

/openapi.yaml         /rates-engine.v1.yaml  200
/openapi.yml          /rates-engine.v1.yaml  200
/spec.yaml            /rates-engine.v1.yaml  200
/spec.yml             /rates-engine.v1.yaml  200

# Versioned alias — pin a major version explicitly so future v2/v3
# can ship alongside without breaking existing v1 consumers.
/v1/openapi.yaml      /rates-engine.v1.yaml  200
